The paper deals with sparsification of graphs and hypergraphs, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science and numerical analysis. The use of probabilistic and deterministic constructions suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CG (computational geometry) sub-categories. The mention of spectral sparsification and the use of matrix analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.NA (numerical analysis) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of the additive sparsification property suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.IT (information theory) sub-category.
